7:["$","article",null,{"className":"min-h-screen bg-white","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12","children":[["$","header",null,{"className":"mb-8","children":[["$","h1",null,{"className":"text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4","children":"Best Internal Auditing Strategy to get ISO 9001 Certification"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"flex items-center gap-4 text-gray-600","children":[["$","time",null,{"dateTime":"2026-01-02T06:30:41+00:00","children":"January 2, 2026"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"inline-block px-3 py-1 bg-blue-100 text-blue-800 rounded-full text-sm","children":"general"}]]}]]}],null,["$","div",null,{"className":"mb-8 p-4 bg-gray-50 rounded-lg border-l-4 border-blue-500","children":["$","p",null,{"className":"text-gray-700 italic","children":"Internal Audit is one of the most vital assessing and analysing tools during implementing ISO 9001 certification for Quality Management System (QMS), or any"}]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"prose prose-lg max-w-none mb-8 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed","children":[["$","p","0",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Best Internal Auditing Strategy to get ISO 9001 Certification"}],["$","p","1",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Internal Audit is one of the most vital assessing and analysing tools during implementing ISO 9001 certification for Quality Management System (QMS), or any other ISO standard pertaining to the management system. An ISO 9001 QMS certification needs are pretty obvious, internal auditing has often become a crucial part of ISO certification for QMS and other standards. Since you are interested to know how the processes in your organization are functioning, your internal audits is an ultimate key resource. Though audit checklists don't seem to be declared as a requirement in the ISO 9001 QMS standard, they are being widely used and vital tool to ensure that when you perform an internal audit on a process you do not miss any parts of that process."}],["$","p","2",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"What are ISO 9001 QMS needs for successful internal audit?"}],["$","p","3",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"To comprehend in a better way the why's and how's of internal audit checklists, it is quite beneficial to know what the ISO 9001 QMS certification requirements concerning why we need to devise periodic internal audits. As per few clauses ISO 9001 standard, the internal audit is mainly devised to perform two important functions in any organization:"}],["$","p","4",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"To ensure that all existing and newly implemented processes are meeting the scheduled arrangements that an organization has devised for those processes in line with ISO 9001 QMS and any necessities that the ISO certification standard has in place for that process."}],["$","p","5",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"To ensure all processes are successfully implemented and strictly follows ISO 9001 QMS needs and requirements and those are maintained without any hurdles."}],["$","p","6",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"So, when you are drafting an internal audit checklist you should incorporate the data and information required to ensure that you successfully check these 2 outcomes of the process."}],["$","p","7",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"How does one draft an internal audit checklist to ascertain conformity of ISO 9001 QMS?"}],["$","p","8",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"An internal audit is predominantly implemented to ascertain the efficiency and result of a process through a thorough review of records or witnessing the actions of your organization's work force, which is then compared with the scheduled arrangements for your organization's process to check if what is being done is what was planned. As mentioned above, there are two sets of planned and scheduled arrangements to check: improvements needed by ISO 9001 QMS standard and improvements or modification that an organization has put in place for their process to operate."}],"$L10","$L11","$L12","$L13","$L14","$L15","$L16"]}],"$L17"]}]}]
